b697cbe2-0775-59ae-a1d0-4ecbcaca385b,tg:rubgr:3171,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"[recto] Hochzeitszug, Northwick Park. [Max J.] Friedländer, Bruegel [= Pieter Bruegel, Berlin: Propyläen], 1921, citaat p. 108; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. Like Friedländer and Glück who for a long time could not decide whether to accept this painting as an original (work of B.) which in the end they did. I was rather in doubt about its authorship when the first time Capt. Sp. Ch. kindly permitted me to study the picture at Northwick Park. Its high qaulity made a decission most difficult. Recent and prolonged examin at the Flemish Exhibition where it hung near the P... by Jan Br. from Windsor Castle made it clear ...' [sic]; [verso] [Max J.] Friedländer, [= Die altniederländische Malerei], XIV, [Leiden: Sijthoff],1937, citaten pp. 33, 60.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>[recto] Hochzeitszug, Northwick Park. [Max J.] Friedländer, Bruegel [= Pieter Bruegel, Berlin: Propyläen], 1921, citaat p. 108; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. Like Friedländer and Glück who for a long time could not decide whether to accept this painting as an original (work of B.) which in the end they did. I was rather in doubt about its authorship when the first time Capt. Sp. Ch. kindly permitted me to study the picture at Northwick Park. Its high qaulity made a decission most difficult. Recent and prolonged examin at the Flemish Exhibition where it hung near the P... by Jan Br. from Windsor Castle made it clear ...' [sic]; [verso] [Max J.] Friedländer, [= Die altniederländische Malerei], XIV, [Leiden: Sijthoff],1937, citaten pp. 33, 60.</content>
